		<header class="comment-header">
			<p class="comment-author">
				<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/edcbe82e36a8f231bdac596c1d23164a?s=48&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/edcbe82e36a8f231bdac596c1d23164a?s=96&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' loading='lazy'/><span itemprop="name"><a href="http://www.solidliftparts.com/" class="comment-author-link" rel="external nofollow" itemprop="url">Louie Lorenzana</a></span> 			</p>

			<p class="comment-meta"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-01-14T03:06:00-08:00" itemprop="datePublished"><a href="https://blog.sucuri.net/2012/08/secure-website-development-importance-of-developing-securely.html#comment-2108">January 14, 2014</a></time></p>		</header>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Web applications present designers and developers with many challenges.<br />
The stateless nature of HTTP means that tracking per-user session state<br />
becomes the responsibility of the application. As a precursor to this,<br />
the application must be able to identify the user by using some form of<br />
authentication.</p>
		</div>

		
		
	</article>
	</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ol></div></main><aside class="sidebar sidebar-primary widget-area" role="complementary" aria-label="Primary Sidebar" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/WPSideBar" id="genesis-sidebar-primary"><h2 class="genesis-sidebar-title screen-reader-text">Primary Sidebar</h2><div class="sidebar-primary-wrap"><section id="text-5" class="widget widget_text"><div class="widget-wrap"><h3 class="widgettitle widget-title">Socialize With Sucuri</h3>
